Prints an object to the console with a trailing newline.
```dart
print('Hello World');
print(42);
print([1, 2, 3]);
```

Parses a string as a double. Throws `FormatException` if invalid.
```dart
double d = double.parse('3.14');
double d2 = double.parse('1e10');
```

Creates a future that completes after the given duration.
```dart
await Future.delayed(Duration(seconds: 2));
var result = await Future.delayed(Duration(seconds: 1), () => 42);
```

Creates a stream from an iterable of elements.
```dart
var stream = Stream.fromIterable([1, 2, 3]);
await for (var value in stream) {
  print(value);
}
```

Creates a regular expression from a pattern string.
```dart
var re = RegExp(r'\d+');
var match = re.firstMatch('abc123');
var allMatches = re.allMatches('a1 b2 c3');
```

Returns the current date and time in the local time zone.
```dart
var now = DateTime.now();
print(now.year);
print(now.toIso8601String());
```

Creates a duration from named components.
```dart
var d = Duration(hours: 1, minutes: 30);
var d2 = Duration(days: 7);
print(d.inMinutes); // 90
```

Parses a JSON string and returns the decoded object.
```dart
import 'dart:convert';
var data = jsonDecode('{"name": "Alice", "age": 30}');
print(data['name']); // Alice
```

Converts an object to a JSON string.
```dart
import 'dart:convert';
var json = jsonEncode({'name': 'Alice', 'age': 30});
print(json); // {"name":"Alice","age":30}
```
